{"abstract": "Some lawmakers in Washington want to alter President Obama\u2019s banking regulation proposal to look more like Glass-Steagall, a move that if successful would have a profound impact on the face of Wall Street.", "web_url": "https://dealbook.nytimes.com/2010/01/22/yearning-for-glass-steagall-on-capitol-hill/", "snippet": "Some lawmakers in Washington want to alter President Obama\u2019s banking regulation proposal to look more like Glass-Steagall, a move that if successful would have a profound impact on the face of Wall Street.", "lead_paragraph": "President Obama\u2019s plan to rein in big banks and their ability to make risky bets may seem to hark back to the days when commercial banking and investment banking were separated by the Depression-era Glass-Steagall Act. But the so-called Volcker Rule, as Mr. Obama\u2019s proposal is known, does not go as far as Glass-Steagall in that it would allow commercial banks to retain some investment banking activities, like underwriting securities and trading on behalf of clients.", "source": "The New York Times", "multimedia": [], "headline": {"main": "Yearning for Glass-Steagall on Capitol Hill", "kicker": "DealBook", "content_kicker": null, "print_headline": "", "name": null, "seo": null, "sub": null}, "keywords": [{"name": "persons", "value": "Cantwell, Maria", "rank": 1, "major": "N"}, {"name": "persons", "value": "Dodd, Christopher J", "rank": 2, "major": "N"}, {"name": "persons", "value": "Frank, Barney", "rank": 3, "major": "N"}, {"name": "persons", "value": "Johnson, Tim", "rank": 4, "major": "N"}, {"name": "persons", "value": "Kanjorski, Paul E", "rank": 5, "major": "N"}, {"name": "persons", "value": "KAUFMAN, TED", "rank": 6, "major": "N"}, {"name": "persons", "value": "McCain, John", "rank": 7, "major": "N"}, {"name": "persons", "value": "Obama, Barack", "rank": 8, "major": "N"}, {"name": "persons", "value": "Shelby, Richard C", "rank": 9, "major": "N"}, {"name": "persons", "value": "Volcker, Paul A"